# Sara LXXIX.: Nāzi’āt, or Those Who Tear Out.

### Section 2

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_027.gif)

27. Aantum ashaddu khalqan ami a**l**ssam<u>a</u>o ban<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

27\. What! Are ye the more  
Difficult to create  
Or the heaven (above)?  
(God) hath constructed it:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_028.gif)

28. RafaAAa samkah<u>a</u> fasaww<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

28\. On high hath He raised  
Its canopy, and He hath  
Given it order and perfection.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_029.gif)

29. Waagh<u>t</u>asha laylah<u>a</u> waakhraja
<u>d</u>u<u>ha</u>h<u>a</u>

29\. Its night doth He  
Endow with darkness,  
And its splendour doth He  
Bring out (with light).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_030.gif)

30. Wa**a**l-ar<u>d</u>a baAAda <u>tha</u>lika da<u>ha</u>h<u>a</u>

30\. And the earth, moreover,  
Hath He extended  
(To a wide expanse);

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_031.gif)

31. Akhraja minh<u>a</u> m<u>a</u>ah<u>a</u> wamarAA<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

31\. He draweth out  
Therefrom its moisture  
And its pasture;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_032.gif)

32. Wa**a**ljib<u>a</u>la ars<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

32\. And the mountains  
Hath He firmly fixed;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_033.gif)

33. Mat<u>a</u>AAan lakum wali-anAA<u>a</u>mikum

33\. For use and convenience  
To you and your cattle.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_034.gif)

34. Fa-i<u>tha</u> j<u>a</u>ati a**l**<u>tta</u>mmatu alkubr<u>a</u>

34\. Therefore, when there comes  
The great, overwhelming (Event),—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_035.gif)

35. Yawma yata<u>th</u>akkaru al-ins<u>a</u>nu m<u>a</u> saAA<u>a</u>

35\. The Day when Man  
Shall remember (all)  
That he strove for,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_036.gif)

36. Waburrizati alja<u>h</u>eemu liman yar<u>a</u>

36\. And Hell-Fire shall be  
Placed in full view  
For (all) to see,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_037.gif)

37. Faamm<u>a</u> man <u>t</u>agh<u>a</u>

37\. Then, for such as had  
Transgressed all bounds,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_038.gif)

38. Wa<u>a</u>thara al<u>h</u>ay<u>a</u>ta a**l**dduny<u>a</u>

38\. And had preferred  
The life of this world,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_039.gif)

39. Fa-inna alja<u>h</u>eema hiya alma/w<u>a</u>

39\. The Abode will be  
Hell-Fire;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_040.gif)

40. Waam<u>a</u> man kh<u>a</u>fa maq<u>a</u>ma rabbihi wanah<u>a</u>
a**l**nnafsa AAani alhaw<u>a</u>

40\. And for such as had  
Entertained the fear  
Of standing before  
Their Lord's (tribunal)  
And had restrained  
(Their) soul from lower Desires,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_041.gif)

41. Fa-inna aljannata hiya alma/w<u>a</u>

41\. Their Abode will be  
The Garden.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_042.gif)

42. Yas-aloonaka AAani a**l**ss<u>a</u>AAati ayy<u>a</u>na
murs<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

42\. They ask thee  
About the Hour,—"When  
Will be its appointed time?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_043.gif)

43. Feema anta min <u>th</u>ikr<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

43\. Wherein art thou (concerned)  
With the declaration thereof?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_044.gif)

44. Il<u>a</u> rabbika muntah<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

44\. With thy Lord is  
The Limit fixed therefor.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_045.gif)

45. Innam<u>a</u> anta mun<u>th</u>iru man yakhsh<u>a</u>h<u>a</u>

45\. Thou art but a Warner  
For such as fear it.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/079/079_046.gif)

46. Kaannahum yawma yarawnah<u>a</u> lam yalbathoo ill<u>a</u>
AAashiyyatan aw <u>d</u>u<u>ha</u>h<u>a</u>

46\. The Day they see it,  
(It will be) as if they  
Had tarried but a single  
Evening, or (at most till)  
The following morn!

